	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_UHLAN">
			<Text>Uhlan</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_UHLAN_HELP">
			<Text>Mounted Unit capable of fighting toe-to-toe with contemporary infantry units. Only Poland may build it.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_UHLAN_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Uhlan is a Polish unique unit. Unlike the Cavalry it replaces, the Uhlan get a strong combat bonus against melee units and while in open terrain.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_UHLAN_TEXT">
			<Text>
				Uhlans were Polish light cavalry armed with lances, sabres and pistols. After Poland's independence in 1918, Uhlan formations were raised in all parts of the country. They fought with distinction in the Greater Poland Uprising, the Polish-Ukrainian War and the Polish-Bolshevik War. Although equipped with modern horse-drawn artillery and trained in infantry tactics, the Uhlan formations kept their sabres, their lances and their ability to charge the enemy. Among other battles, the Uhlan units took part in the Battle of Komarów of 1920 against the invading Soviet Konarmia, the last pure cavalry battle in history.
			</Text>
		</Row>

		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_SHOCK_CHARGER">
			<Text>Shock Charger</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_SHOCK_CHARGER_HELP">
			<Text>+15% [ICON_STRENGTH] Combat Strength when fighting in OPEN Terrain. (NO Hills, Forest or Jungle).[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]+33% [ICON_STRENGTH] Combat Strength when fighting Melee and Gun Units.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>

